'''''Naples in Green and Blue''''' (Italian:'''''Napoli verde-blu''''') is a 1935 Italian [[musical film]] directed by [[Armando Fizzarotti]] and starring [[Lina Gennari]], [[Ellen Meis]] and [[Silvio Orsini]].<ref>Liehm p.22</ref> Although set in [[Naples]], the film was shot in a studio in [[Rome]].<ref>Marlow-Mann p.16</ref> It was a low-budget [[revue]], featuring a series of popular performers.

